{"id": 12480, "date": "1987-03-24T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-03-24T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=12480"}, "modified": "2026-06-10T13:42:04", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-10T20:42:04", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-and-jimmy-fallon-whip-my-hair", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/03/24/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-jimmy-fallon-whip-my-hair/", "title": {"rendered": "Whip My Hair"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce Springsteen has performed a lot of unlikely covers across his long and illustrious career, but I&#8217;m not sure that anyone would have ever predicted this one, let alone on television and as an official CD release.</p>\n<p>In the autumn and winter of 2010, ten-year-old Willow Smith&#8217;s debut single &#8220;Whip My Hair&#8221; was\u00a0<em>everywhere</em>. Whether you liked it or hated it, odds are that you couldn&#8217;t get it out of your head no matter how hard you tried.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/kMhUt5Y7fNc?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>So when Bruce made an appearance on\u00a0<em>Late Night with Jimmy Fallon</em> at the height of the song&#8217;s popularity, Bruce and Jimmy conspired to blow fans&#8217; minds by covering it.</p>\n<p>Bruce was already a fan of Jimmy&#8217;s Neil Young impression, so they decided to make it a duet with Jimmy in character. Bruce and Jimmy collaborated an arrangement that parodied a typical Springsteen concert arrangement, but the idea for Springsteen to perform as &#8220;1975 Bruce&#8221; was entirely Bruce&#8217;s.</p>\n<p>Listen to Jimmy tell the story:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/o_cFobBHYqU?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>And yes, when Bruce walked out on stage for the cold open that night, the crowd (and almost certainly, the entirety of E Street Nation) did indeed go nuts. The result&#8230; well, it may not be one of Bruce&#8217;s best covers, but it&#8217;s certainly one of his most viral.</p>\n<div id=\"v-ETduz4Hn-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/ETduz4Hn?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p>What did Bruce think of the performance? Let&#8217;s follow him backstage and find out:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/nKtm2g6Pp_w?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Eighteen months later, Bruce still must have felt pretty good about that performance, because he gave Fallon permission to release the recording on Jimmy&#8217;s second album,\u00a0<em>Blow Your Pants Off. </em>(Their duet is the closing track on that 2012 album.)</p>\n<p>Bruce and &#8220;Neil&#8221; would also reprise their performance two years (and ten fashion years) later, this time covering &#8220;Sexy and I Know It.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Even so, I wouldn&#8217;t bet on Bruce picking a sign for &#8220;Whip My Hair&#8221; anytime soon. That was almost certainly a one-time-only experience.</p>\n<p><strong>Whip My Hair<br />\nRecorded: </strong>November 16, 2010<strong><br />\nReleased:\u00a0</strong><em>Blow Your Pants Off\u00a0</em>(2012)<strong><br />\nFirst performed:</strong>\u00a0November 16, 2010 (New York City, NY)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> November 16, 2010 (New York City, NY)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 September 5, 2019</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce and Jimmy Fallon (as Neil Young) perform the unlikeliest of covers in one of Bruce&#8217;s most viral moments. Watch the performance and backstory inside.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69835, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [4, 3617, 5], "tags": [2454, 52, 2455, 510, 1881], "class_list": ["post-12480", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-it-takes-two", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-blow-your-pants-off", "tag-jimmy-fallon", "tag-late-night-with-jimmy-fallon", "tag-neil-young", "tag-whip-my-hair"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/admin-ajax-2026-06-10T134056.095.jpg?fit=1000%2C1000&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-3fi", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 1227, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/03/01/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-jimmy-fallon-sexy-and-i-know-it/", "url_meta": {"origin": 12480, "position": 0}, "title": "Sexy and I Know It", "author": "Ken", "date": "March 1, 1987", "format": false, "excerpt": "A self-spoofing Bruce joins Jimmy Fallon-as-Neil Young for a hilarious take on LMFAO's \"Sexy and I Know It.\"", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;It Takes Two&quot;", "block_context": {"text": "It Takes Two", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/category/it-takes-two/"}, "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/360295-120305-ent-fallon-springsteen.webp?fit=1000%2C660&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200, "srcset": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/360295-120305-ent-fallon-springsteen.webp?fit=1000%2C660&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200 1x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/upl